<p>Vanderweil Facilities Advisors
(VFA) is the preemeinant supplier
of software and services to organizations
with extensive property
holdings and large deferred maintenance
budgets.  Their customer
list includes such organizations as
MIT, the Fedreal Government, and
the States of Texas and New
Jersey. Although the company's
facilty assessment services and
cost forcasting applications were
still effective, customers were
demanding a web-based solution
with expanded capabilities.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Requirements</font>

<p>VFA originally
hired Nevo to review current solutions
and customer requirements,
and then design a next-generation
system that would meet changing
needs while providing a platform
for growth.  In the course of the
design effort, however, it became
obviois that VFA's in-house
resources would be insufficient to
meet their near-term customer
commitments.  Nevo's role was
therefore expanded to include
customization of the company's
existing product as well as design
and implementation of the next-generation
product.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Nevo's Solution</font>

<p>The original
VFA product was a two-tiered
client/server solution built with
Visual Basic as the dominant programming
language and Oracle
the primary database.  The next-generation
design continues the
use of Oracle, but introduces a
multi-tiered architecture.  Clients
are now browser-based, using
JavaScript and DHTML for local
processing.  Because the VFA
organization is particularly comfortable
with the Microsoft toolset,
server side development relies on
ASP, Microsoft Transaction
Server, COM objects, and ActiveX
components.  Nevo stepped directly
into this critical customer delivery
situation and successfully met VFA's commitments&#8212;on time.




